Reweighting and Reconstruction Workﬂow

In the N V T ensemble, the general case for applying the reweighting and reconstruction scheme
is to predict an ensemble average A∗ can at certain temperature and density that are diﬀerent
from the ones used to generate the MC Markov chain. In other words, the general case will
be to extrapolate ensemble averages along paths of changing temperature and density at same
time. This is possible by ﬁrst reconstructing and then reweighting the original sampled Markov
chain using the following relation
