along isotherms. It is possible to extrapolate from a certain source point to other neighboring
points at both diﬀerent temperature and pressure conditions. As an example (Figure 5), source
points (◦) along β ∗ = 0.3 were used to extrapolate points (·) at diﬀerent pressures along two
diﬀerent isotherms β ∗ = 0.25 ( ) and 0.35 ( ). The symbols ( and ) are only plotted to show
